'''''Wild Seasons: Gathering and Cooking Wild Plants of the Great Plains''''' is a 1993 non-fiction book by author, illustrator, and [[Ethnobotany|ethno-botanist]] Kay Young.<ref name="amazon.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/nebraska/9780803299047/|title=Wild Seasons: Gathering and Cooking Wild Plants of the Great Plains|author=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|isbn=9780803299047|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=}}</ref> It features a variety of wild plants of the great plains area and how to prepare them in appetizing ways.<ref name="unl">{{cite web|url=http://arboretum.unl.edu/documents/The%20Seed%20Edible%20Landscapes%202010.pdf|date=20 June 2013|title=The Seed Nebraska Statewide Arboretum, Inc.  |accessdate=2016-03-16}}</ref> The book includes a number of recipes as well as Young's enthusiasm and advocacy for eating wild crops. It was published by the [[University of Nebraska Press]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/nebraska/9780803299047/|title=Wild Seasons - University of Nebraska Press|work=Nebraska Press|access-date=2017-11-04|language=en-US}}</ref>

